The paper deals with the problem of estimating a random vector from noisy linear measurements, which is a common problem in statistical learning and linear inverse problems. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including Information Theory (cs.IT), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Signal Processing (cs.SP), Multimedia (cs.MM), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The paper's focus on message-passing algorithms and their convergence properties further supports these sub-categories.
